body:
### Problem

Consider the API Info of nvim_tabpage_list_wins:
```json
  {
    "name": "nvim_tabpage_list_wins",
    "since": 1,
    "parameters": [
      [
        "Tabpage",
        "tabpage"
      ]
    ],
    "return_type": "ArrayOf(Window)",
    "method": true
  },
```
The return type is presented as a string (`ArrayOf(Window)`). This forces API client generators to parse type strings in order to be able to generate well-typed functions.

An improvement could be:
```json
  {
    "name": "nvim_tabpage_list_wins",
    "since": 1,
    "parameters": [
      [
        "Tabpage",
        "tabpage"
      ]
    ],
    "return_type": {
      "name": "Array",
      "parameters": [
          {"name": "Window"}
      ]
    },
    "method": true
  },
```
The reason we want `parameters` to be an array of types is for tuples and enumerations. Tuples are currently presented as:
```json
  {
    "name": "nvim_win_get_cursor",
    "since": 1,
    "parameters": [
      [
        "Window",
        "window"
      ]
    ],
    "return_type": "ArrayOf(Integer, 2)",
    "method": true
  },
```
But it would be nicer if they were:
```json
  {
    "name": "nvim_win_get_cursor",
    "since": 1,
    "parameters": [
      [
        "Window",
        "window"
      ]
    ],
    "return_type": {
        "name": "Tuple",
        "parameters": [
            {"name": "Integer"},
            {"name": "Integer"}
        ]
    },
    "method": true
  },
```
This would enable describing arbitrary-length tuples whose types mismatch.
